INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS FOR THE MOZART ENGINE
===============================================
(see also ../INSTALL)

- Requirements

    GNU gmp library

- Configure options

The default is such that an optimized system is generated.a

  --enable-opt
     default is to compile with maximal optimization ($oz_copt_optimize)

     --enable-opt=d
        compile with debug switches ($oz_copt_debug)

     --enable-opt=p
        compile with profiling switches ($oz_copt_profile)

  --with-pgcc
     use Pentium GCC if available

  --with-gmp=<dir> use gmp.h and libgmp.{a,so} found in <dir>

  --with-gmp-lib=<dir> use libgmp.{a,so} found in <dir>

  --with-gmp-include=<dir> use gmp.h found in <dir>

  --with-malloc=<obj> use malloc() from <obj>

- Environment variables used by configure

 - CC: the C compiler

 - CXX: the C++ compiler

 - LDFLAGS: additional linker options (e.g. -L<libdir>)

 - CPPFLAGS: additional preprocessor options (e.g. -DDEBUG_P)

 - CFLAGS: additional compiler options

 - oz_copt_optimize: compiler options if $oz_enable-opt=yes
 - oz_copt_debug:    compiler options if $oz_enable-opt=d*
 - oz_copt_profile:  compiler options if $oz_enable-opt=p*
 - oz_warn:          compiler options for warnings
 - oz_warn_error:    compiler option to turn warnings into errors
 - oz_lopt_profile:  linker options if  $oz_enable-opt=p*
 - oz_gmp_inc_dir
 - oz_gmp_lib_dir
 - oz_enable_peanuts
 - oz_malloc_obj
 - oz_tmphack_host
 - oz_enable_threaded
 - oz_enable_fastreg
 - oz_enable_regopt

- At compile time 'make CUSR=...' can be used to set additional
  compiler switches (e.g. make CUSR="-DMM").

- If -Werror option of gcc causes trouble use 'make OZ_WARN_ERROR=' to
  avoid that warnings are treated as errors.
